 sign (\u2212), forward arrow (\u25B6), backward arrow (\u25C0), and others indicative of navigation and functionality. Below the header, there are three empty text input fields where users can enter priority items or attributes. The interface appears to be designed for data entry, possibly related to task or item prioritization within a project management or organizational tool.\n\n\n  \n What\u2019s important in the screen details are the  Data Source ,  Name , and the selection of all existing screen sections in the  Toolbox : \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/1/19b9f2f497eb37e7846d4f86e618add5562b3436.png]\nDescription: The image displays a user interface panel labeled \u0022Screen: Priority.\u0022 It includes fields for \u0022Data Source,\u0022 \u0022Name,\u0022 \u0022Id,\u0022 and \u0022Package,\u0022 with text indicating \u0022Priority\u0022 as both the Data Source and Name, and a unique identifier \u0022a481daa1-dbf1-496b-bd36-a788beccdd\u0022 listed under Id, while \u0022myapplication\u0022 is shown as the Package. In the toolbox section, there are two categories: \u0022Screen Sections\u0022 and \u0022Widgets,\u0022 with items including \u0022param_lookup,\u0022 \u0022param_string,\u0022 \u0022Priority,\u0022 \u0022SD_WorkQueue_Select,\u0022 \u0022UserPermissionsOverview,\u0022 and \u0022UserProfile\u0022 visible. The overall purpose of this panel appears to be for configuring elements related to the Priority screen in an application development environment.\n\n\n  \n   Screen Section overview \n Let\u2019s take a closer look at the screen section the wizard created for us. \n Here, you can again see the  Data Source ,  Name , and the  Toolbox , which contains all the fields of the entity: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/b/b7870aa8eec4e5682ff9e6134d873ecf78335bae.png]\nDescription: The image depicts a user interface for a software application section titled \u0022Priority.\u0022 It includes a data source labeled \u0022Priority\u0022 with an associated ID (0f23ee3f-6814-4955-b8ac-07a8c457dc) and package name \u0022myapplication.\u0022 The left sidebar features a toolbox with widgets such as _mockPk, Color, Id, Name, Order, RecordCreated, RecordCreatedBy, RecordUpdated, RecordUpdatedBy, and Selected. The main area displays a form with three empty input fields labeled \u0022Name,\u0022 \u0022Color,\u0022 and \u0022Order.\u0022 The top of the interface contains navigation buttons, with a status indicator showing \u00220 / 0.\u0022 The overall purpose appears to be for data entry or management related to priority settings within the application.\n\n\n  \n   Data Structure overview \n The last artifact created by the wizard is the data structure: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/0/01329081eceda35a4a9bb10195acc92604e0dd55.png]\nDescription: The image displays a Model Browser interface within a software application, showcasing the hierarchical structure of a project labeled \u0022myapplication.\u0022 The sections include \u0022Common,\u0022 \u0022Data,\u0022 and \u0022Constants,\u0022 with a subcategory for \u0022Data Structures.\u0022 Under \u0022myapplication,\u0022 two items are listed: \u0022LookupPriority_Name_GetId\u0022 and another \u0022LookupPriority_Name_GetId.\u0022 The \u0022Entities\u0022 section features \u0022Priority\u0022 along with organizational categories like \u0022Organization Management\u0022 and \u0022Partner Management.\u0022 The interface appears to facilitate navigation and organization of data elements within the application.\n\n\n  \n   Manual procedure \n Since screens are composed of screen sections, we need to create those first. \n   Screen Section creation \n In the Model Browser under  User Interface  /  Screen Sections , right-click on the package folder of your application and select  New  /  Screen Section : \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/c/c56675d1c061353352e274dfe5ff651f22c7073a.png]\nDescription: The image depicts a user interface for a Model Browser in an application titled \u0022myapplication.\u0022 The left panel is organized into categories: \u0022Common,\u0022 \u0022Data,\u0022 and \u0022User Interface.","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-05-01T23:48:38"},"vector":[-0.045980733,-0.008999538,-0.07309673,-0.008715724,0.023758862,-0.007563142,-0.0049967514,0.01366028,0.012378569,0.010385939,0.018928511,-0.00536643,0.014504828,0.014852781,0.00846826,0.03220826,0.029507684,0.019329365,0.03555315,0.018093443,-0.003449462,-0.012497512,0.044337958,0.023130156,-0.0010465736,0.045010775,0.03569742,-0.023347406,-0.00017549198,0.010984025,0.0106890695,-0.061321076,0.014968467,-0.004240239,-0.022021774,-0.024561444,0.0033516297,-0.020937491,-0.03743744,0.0036207098,-0.029494757,0.009498567,-0.009813034,0.020308072,-0.026277497,-0.03831084,0.014127087,-0.0049362583,0.0134637235,-0.019347768,-0.039916977,-0.015373901,0.049629077,-0.021280743,0.05545516,0.036681086,-0.031024426,-0.004598919,-0.038979564,0.039480135,-0.028069083,0.0073691867,0.022793759,-0.015558406,0.017390551,0.015656995,-0.044447135,-0.01742335,-0.032683514,-0.016380154,-0.003692809,0.033752605,-0.05136873,-0.0151346885,-0.07210036,0.027108472,-0.03498207,-0.00368637,-0.07296566,0.04100647,-0.017667314,-0.010312314,-0.0087265,0.017564828,0.029110821,0.029170541,-0.03428806,0.11331905,0.028912282,0.0061044223,-0.024959505,-0.0023426146,0.09792446,-0.056658085,-0.00072458497,0.015710197,-0.036823526,-0.026846286,0.015463957,0.008991503,-0.028328026,-0.032193456,-0.029586079,-0.023550544,0.008298926,-0.010474247,0.029326938,-0.009537367,-0.04930171,-0.04704602,0.00216905,0.03405225,0.015765728,0.0071918876,-0.0039244643,-0.0010131007,0.00807012,-0.0151655795,0.009235614,0.028754618,-0.029725607,0.045704395,0.055713594,-0.00979191,0.018341482,-0.02097246,-0.0